        <section aria-labelledby="corporate-information-heading">
          <h1 id="corporate-information-heading">Corporate information</h1>
          <p>Appears under the ‘Corporate information’ heading on the organisation home page. Generally, content organisations have to publish this information to meet a specific government commitment.</p>
          <h2>Quick reference guide: corporate information</h2>
          <p>Tell users what your department actually does. Don't give mission statements and visions – tell users what you are actually doing for them and what you are responsible for.</p>
